# Local (no setup): npm run cert:auto-local

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Sepolia public testnet (so QR codes verify from any phone, anywhere)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Get a free RPC URL from Alchemy or Infura:
#      https://dashboard.alchemy.com → Apps → Create App → Network: Ethereum Sepolia
#    Copy the HTTPS URL it gives you.
SEPOLIA_RPC_URL=https://eth-sepolia.g.alchemy.com/v2/YOUR_KEY

# 2. Use a NEW MetaMask wallet (never your main one). Export its private key:
#      MetaMask → ⋮ → Account details → Show private key
#    Then fund it with free Sepolia ETH from a faucet, e.g.:
#      https://sepoliafaucet.com
#      https://www.alchemy.com/faucets/ethereum-sepolia
#    You only need ~0.05 SEPOLIA ETH for deploy + lots of issuances.
DEPLOYER_PRIVATE_KEY=0xYOUR_TESTNET_PRIVATE_KEY

# 3. Deploy + sync FRONTEND/.env in one shot:
#      cd blockchain
#      npm run cert:auto-sepolia
#
# 4. Add CERT_ISSUER_PRIVATE_KEY=<same key as above> to FRONTEND/.env
#    (server-only, not exposed to the browser; signs the issue() calls).
#
# 5. On Vercel: set the same four env vars (VITE_CERT_REGISTRY_ADDRESS,
#    VITE_CERT_REGISTRY_RPC_URL, CERT_REGISTRY_ADDRESS, CERT_REGISTRY_RPC_URL)
#    plus CERT_ISSUER_PRIVATE_KEY in Project Settings → Environment Variables.
#    Redeploy.
